<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id602f32f7-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58" identifier="/us/usc/t30/s1027"><num value="1027">§ 1027.</num><heading> Land subject to prohibition on leasing</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall not issue any lease under this chapter on those lands subject to the prohibition provided under <ref href="/us/usc/t30/s226–3">section 226–3 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id602f32f8-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/581/s29">Pub. L. 91–581, § 29</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/100/443/s5/d">Pub. L. 100–443, § 5(d)</ref>, <date date="1988-09-22">Sept. 22, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/1769">102 Stat. 1769</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/109/58/tII/s236/27">Pub. L. 109–58, title II, § 236(27)</ref>, <date date="2005-08-08">Aug. 8, 2005</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/119/673">119 Stat. 673</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
